<br>
Once we got the tamer to us, we had a 60 chanter use his highest charm spell (the mob is level 52) to charm it. It conned indifferent to me once charmed and I handed in the gem of persuasion. I then turned in the giant gem and the blood wolf harness. I got back the giant harness of control. I did not get back the blood wolf harness. Once I had my giant harness, we broke the charm and killed the tamer. Then we looted and the blood wolf harness was on the dead tamer. I let a shaman who needed the leggings loot the harness.<br>
<br>
I turned in the harness to the broodmother and followed her down to the cave. I had SoE up and it wasn't long before the chase for Korf was on. I'd say it was a close race, but I managed to get enough distance to him to aggro him with a root. Then he quickly succombed to my dots. I do have to say the extended affliction 3 item has been one of my best asset in root/dotting mobs for exp since gaining it. <p>Fyrth Pineneedle (59 Preserver)<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90197 " target="_blank">Magelo Profile<BR>
